annotation.TEXT: And now to slowly swim all the way back.
We've got "Monty Mole Hills"...
And just like in EVW, there's absolutely nothing over here!
Now, let's go the way I was probably meant to go.
Doesn't look like it. If only I had a cape, then I could do what I did in many places of EVW, and check out the probably empty area over there.
Oh, Yoshi, don't swallow the key! (Why'd I even bring that with me over here?)
Nuts. Failed on the recycling attempt. Oh, well.
More RVFs... I'll just fry them from a distance!
Huh? This area again? And this time I don't think there was a way for me to have gotten 30 coins during the level...
Oh, a bonus room, eh? But, what's the deal with the screen scrolling to the right?
Nope, nothing! And now to slowly swim all the way back...
Alright, time to TAS this sucker!
Alright, so I've unlocked two more levels here.
D'oh! Well I screwed that up! (Also, I notice that by duck-jumping in certain spots, I could've potentially gone through all three paths in one go, but with Yoshi, that probably wasn't gonna happen.)
Success!!!
And now to quickly get the normal exit, which I assume is through that pipe I saw.
At least the game gave me that hint, so I wouldn't be stuck here thinking I was trapped or something!
And now, with the power of flight, I can do the EVW thing that I mentioned before!
...and "Messy Treehouse".
So, we're in an elevator shaft I guess, and since I have to do some climbing, I'll probably have to ditch Yoshi, but let's see how far I can take him...
Okay, so this level's cleared, but I'm not quite done with it yet...
Going down...
Well, I think I know how that happened, but why was this type of room in the original game created with its right wall going one space farther than necessary?
Well, so much for that shell. Anything to the left?

Nuts. It doesn't look like I'm getting enough height. Maybe I could make it with a midair P-switch jump, but I'm not going to bother with that now, and the goal sphere's probably not important anyway.
Well, that's not good... But, I'm not about to let this stop me!
Well, I found the secret exit, but is there anything further to the right? I just gotta know...
Now, as for the goal sphere in this level... It was suggested that I try Yoshi jumping over the ceiling from the right, so let's try that.
And I get deposited here again, but this time, I have collected 30 coins! So, I guess the route choice at the start didn't really matter, but the path to the right is more rewarding.
I seriously doubt it, but is there anything interesting over here?
Gulp! Uh, oh!
RVF almost cost me Yoshi, but the blurps aren't much more than seafood to me.
But first, there's something in a previous level that I want to check out. I'm going to need a Yoshi for this...
Hey, it's nice of you to not crush this castle after I cleared it though (maybe because it's more like a regular level, being Yoshi-legal and all). Now, let's go to the right this time.
Well, the land suddenly cuts off half a screen before the edge of the area, and there doesn't seem to be anything else over here.
At least I managed to hang onto Yoshi there!
Whoa, right off the bat I'm faced with a Rip Van Fish and a half-dozen Blurps!
Nuts! I missed a coin! ...Or did I? Heh, heh, heh.
Ooh, a disco shell! I can totally use that to check out something!
Good thing I had already hit a goal here! Okay, now let's continue exploring to the right...
Stupid horse...
Which one should I enter next? You guys vote now, and we'll find out next time! To be continued...
Looks like a choice type of thing. I can either choose six coins, nothing, or a 1-up. Well, I think I'll take the 1-up!
Hmm... Left or right? Well, when in doubt, go left. (Where have I heard that before?)
Oh, yuck! Wow, that didn't even remotely look like I was trying for 50 stars!
Barf!
Alright, our first official save point in this game! (Which probably would've been at the switch palace if it weren't for that glitch.)
Oy. Another subpar attempt at the goal tape, though much better than the previous attempt!
And, of course, no Yoshis because... wait, Yoshi's allowed in here? Well, that's more unique than unique castle!
Okay, got the secret exit.
Well, that was a short level, and I didn't find anywhere near 30 coins... Whoa, Yoshi! I hate it when that happens when I'm stomping a jumping enemy!
And I think it's obvious where it'll be used.
Well, there seem to be enough cement blocks for Yoshi to use, and his tongue isn't even glitched, so maybe allowing him in here was intentional.
Oh, boy. Torpedo Teds. This might make things interesting...
Oy. Another subpar attempt at the bonus game, and it's even worse than the previous attempt!
Oh, no! It's a muncher on a short vine! Whatever will we do?! Umm... Jump over it, maybe?
Oh, I see a P-switch down there!
I wonder why that guy was walking away from the shell he was obviously meant to kick... Was he placed in the air in Lunar Magic?
Alright, so I'm done here. Now, let's go on an Undersea Adventure!
But, as expected, it's not a separate exit, so that was all for nothing!
Alright, sorry to waste all of your time with that. Now, let's enter The Great Castle!
Hi, Yoshi! I noticed that the egg seems to have slightly lower gravity when it first pops out. Maybe that's due to its height on the screen?
Quick, bail out with Start+Select!
Hey, maybe there should be a message box on the left route of this level saying something like "My statistics show about 70% of the people go to the right first."
Hello, and welcome back to DODODO's "Mini Levels"! Today, we'll be exploring The Great Castle!
Huh? Well that's odd. The midway gate reappeared. Was it inserted as a Map16 tile instead of as an object?

Oh, but there's more. My route also has three coins in it, while the "nothing" route would've given me a mushroom, which I can still have anyway thanks to Yoshi. Let me just make sure I don't lose my reserve flower...
